<module>
    <h>trang</h>
    <!-- behaviour adjective -->
    <p><g>trang</g>
        <adj/>
        <en>busy</en></p>

    <section>
        <h>nouns</h>
        <section id="nouns-people">
            <h>people</h>
            <p>Examples with proper nouns – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <a href="?gd=Calum">Calum</a> sgìth – tha e ag obair gu trang anns
                            an achadh.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm is tired – he is working busily in the field.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <a href="?gd=maairi">Màiri</a> agus <a href="?gd=calum">Calum</a>
                            trang an diugh – tha iad ag obair anns an achadh.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary and Malcolm are busy today – they are working in the field.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p>Examples with first and second person pronouns – <ul>
                    <li>first person – <ul>
                            <li>singular <g href="?gd=mi">mi</g>
                                <en>I, me</en> – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Tha mi trang.</gd>
                                        <tr>I am busy.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                            <li>plural <g href="?gd=sinn">sinn</g>
                                <en>we, us</en> – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Tha sinn trang.</gd>
                                        <tr>We are busy.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Bha sinn trang ag obair.</gd>
                                        <tr>We were busy working.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 9 [adapted]</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>second person – <ul>
                            <li>singular <g href="?gd=thu">thu</g>
                                <en>you, thou, thee</en> – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Tha thu trang.</gd>
                                        <tr>You are busy.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                            <li>plural <g href="?gd=sibh">sibh</g>
                                <en>you</en> – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Tha sibh trang ag obair anns an achadh agus tha sibh
                                            sgìth.</gd>
                                        <tr>You are busy working in the field and you are
                                            tired.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>An robh sibh trang? Bha.</gd>
                                        <tr>Were you busy? Yes, we were.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [227] [adapted]</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>Examples with third person pronouns – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Calum sgìth – tha <a href="?gd=e_">e</a> ag obair gu trang anns an
                            achadh.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm is tired – he is working busily in the field.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p>Examples with common nouns – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an <a href="?gd=duine">duine</a> seo trang.</gd>
                        <tr>This man is busy.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 79</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an <a href="?gd=saor^n">saor</a> trang ag obair air an taigh.</gd>
                        <tr>The joiner is busy working on the house.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 65</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha na <a href="?gd=tuathanach">tuathanaich</a> ag obair gu trang anns
                            an achadh an dé.</gd>
                        <tr>The farmers were working busily in the field yesterday.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 75</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="nouns-geography">
            <h>geography</h>
            <p><g>trang ann an <a href="?gd=achadh">achadh</a></g>
                <en>busy in a field</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Màiri agus Calum trang an diugh – tha iad ag obair anns an
                            achadh.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary and Malcolm are busy today – they are working in the field.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>verbs</h>
        <section id="verbs-activities">
            <h>activities</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=obair">obair</a> gu trang</g>
            <en>working busily/hard</en> (cf. <g>trang ag obair</g>
            <en>busy working</en>) – <xl>
                <li>
                    <gd>Tha Calum sgìth – tha e ag obair gu trang anns an achadh.</gd>
                    <tr>Malcolm is tired – he is working busily in the field.</tr>
                    <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <gd>Tha Màiri agus Calum trang an diugh – tha iad ag obair anns an achadh.</gd>
                    <tr>Mary and Malcolm are busy today – they are working in the field.</tr>
                    <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <gd>Tha sibh trang ag obair anns an achadh agus tha sibh sgìth.</gd>
                    <tr>You are busy working in the field and you are tired.</tr>
                    <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                </li>
